{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["PolyLoft"], "type": "title", "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "text": ["Creates new polygons using existing points."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["This node generates meshes of triangles by connecting (i.e.\nlofting/stitching) the points of open or closed faces without adding any\nnew points. Polyloft can also connect groups of unrelated points in a\nsimilar fashion. The faces and the point groups need not have the same\nnumber of points."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["The optional input specifies the rest geometry, typically the copy of\nthe main input at a specific face (usually 1). This forces the point\norder to remain constant throughout the animation and prevents the\ntriangular stitch from popping as the geometry deforms. If you specify\nface or point groups for lofting using rest geometry, make sure they are\ndefined in the second input."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Start stitching at the two closest points, and handle arbitrary\n        face orientation and start vertices"]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Connect Closest Ends"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Fuse neighboring points before stitching"]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "parameters_item", "text": ["Consolidate Points"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Threshold distance for consolidation"]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Distance"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/dist"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["Distance minimization goal:"]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["Default stitching target"]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["2-Point Distance"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "text": ["May help avoid intersections"]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "text": ["3-Point Distance"]}], "container": true, "type": 